### Generate Payload GraphQL Schema with pnpm

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/graphql/graphql-schema.mdx

This command executes the `generate:schema` script from the `@payloadcms/graphql` package, creating a GraphQL schema based on your Payload collections and globals. The schema is typically output to `schema.graphql` by default, or `./graphql/schema.graphql` if a custom path is configured.

```bash
pnpm payload-graphql generate:schema
```

--------------------------------

### Generate Drizzle Schema for Type Safety (Shell)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/sqlite.mdx

This shell command is used to generate the Drizzle database schema from your Payload configuration. Running this command ensures type-safety when interacting with your database through Drizzle, providing auto-completion and compile-time checks for your database queries.

```sh
npx payload generate:db-schema
```

--------------------------------

### Example of Drizzle Schema Generated by Introspection (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/sqlite.mdx

This TypeScript snippet provides an example of a Drizzle schema file (`schema.ts`) that might be generated through Drizzle Introspection. It defines two tables, `users` and `countries`, complete with column definitions, primary keys, and a unique index, demonstrating the structure for integrating existing database schemas.

```ts
import {
  sqliteTable,
  text,
  uniqueIndex,
  integer,
} from 'drizzle-orm/sqlite-core'

export const users = sqliteTable('users', {
  id: integer('id').primaryKey({ autoIncrement: true }),
  fullName: text('full_name'),
  phone: text('phone', { length: 256 }),
})

export const countries = sqliteTable(
  'countries',
  {
    id: integer('id').primaryKey({ autoIncrement: true }),
    name: text('name', { length: 256 }),
  },
  (countries) => {
    return {
      nameIndex: uniqueIndex('name_idx').on(countries.name),
    }
  },
)
```

