### Extend Generated Types with Custom Schema

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/typescript/generating-types.mdx

Extend the generated TypeScript types by providing a function to `typescript.schema`. This function receives the current JSON schema and returns a modified one, allowing for the addition of custom definitions or modifications to existing ones.

```typescript
// payload.config.ts
{
  // ...
  typescript: {
    schema: [
      ({ jsonSchema }) => {
        // Modify the JSON schema here
        jsonSchema.definitions.Test = {
          type: 'object',
          properties: {
            title: { type: 'string' },
            content: { type: 'string' },
          },
          required: ['title', 'content'],
        }
        return jsonSchema
      },
    ]
  }
}
```

