### Extend PayloadCMS Generated TypeScript Schema (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/PLUGIN-DEVELOPMENT.md

This example shows how to augment the automatically generated TypeScript schema in PayloadCMS. It adds custom properties, like `ecommerce` with nested `collections` and their respective string types, to the `jsonSchema` object, making these properties available in the Payload configuration for improved type safety and tooling.

```ts
incomingConfig.typescript = incomingConfig.typescript || {}
incomingConfig.typescript.schema = incomingConfig.typescript.schema || []

incomingConfig.typescript.schema.push((args) => {
  const { jsonSchema } = args

  jsonSchema.properties.ecommerce = {
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
      collections: {
        type: 'object',
        properties: {
          products: { type: 'string' },
          orders: { type: 'string' }
        }
      }
    }
  }

  return jsonSchema
})
```

