### Build Next.js without DB connection using experimental-build-mode

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/production/building-without-a-db-connection.mdx

These commands demonstrate how to build a Next.js application without requiring a database connection during the initial compilation phase. The `--experimental-build-mode compile` flag compiles the code only, while `--experimental-build-mode generate` or `generate-env` can be used later to generate static pages or environment variables when a DB connection is available or not needed, respectively. This is particularly useful for Docker builds where a DB might not be connected initially.

```shell
pnpm next build --experimental-build-mode compile
pnpm next build --experimental-build-mode generate
pnpm next build --experimental-build-mode generate-env
```

