### Opt out of Next.js Static Site Generation (SSG) in route segments

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/production/building-without-a-db-connection.mdx

This TypeScript export allows a specific Next.js route segment to opt out of Static Site Generation, forcing dynamic rendering. While it eliminates the database connection requirement during build, it will disable static optimization and may result in slower page loads. It should be added to the relevant route segment files.

```typescript
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'
```

