### Define Drizzle Schema for Existing Database Tables in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/postgres.mdx

Shows how to define Drizzle schema for existing database tables using Drizzle Introspection. Creates table definitions for users and countries with various column types and indexes, which can be imported into Payload config.

```typescript
import {
  pgTable,
  uniqueIndex,
  serial,
  varchar,
  text,
} from 'drizzle-orm/pg-core'

export const users = pgTable('users', {
  id: serial('id').primaryKey(),
  fullName: text('full_name'),
  phone: varchar('phone', { length: 256 }),
})

export const countries = pgTable(
  'countries',
  {
    id: serial('id').primaryKey(),
    name: varchar('name', { length: 256 }),
  },
  (countries) => {
    return {
      nameIndex: uniqueIndex('name_idx').on(countries.name),
    }
  },
)
```

